
# 1. Count Set Bits

A set bit means a bit whose value is 1.

Example:

11010101


Let's count them.

```text
1 1 0 1 0 1 0 1
↑ ↑   ↑   ↑   ↑

Total = 5
```

## Method 1 (Easy)

Check every bit.

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 0b11010101;   // Binary literal (213 in decimal)

        int count = 0;

        while (n > 0) {
            if ((n & 1) == 1) { // Check last bit
                count++;
            }
            n = n >> 1;         // Remove last bit
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }
}
```

### How it works

Suppose

```text
n = 11010101
```

Iteration 1

```text
11010101
       &
00000001
---------
00000001

count = 1
```

Shift right.

```text
01101010
```

Again

```text
01101010
       &
00000001
---------
00000000

count = 1
```

Keep doing this until `n` becomes 0.

Time Complexity:

```text
O(number of bits)
```

For an `int`, that's at most **32 iterations**.

