## Method 2 (Best Method - Brian Kernighan Algorithm)

This is asked in interviews.

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int n = 0b11010101;

        int count = 0;

        while (n != 0) {
            n = n & (n - 1);
            count++;
        }

        System.out.println(count);
    }
}
```

### Why does it work?

Take

```text
11010101
```

Subtract one

```text
11010100
```

Now AND

```text
11010101
11010100
--------
11010100
```

The **rightmost 1 disappears**.

Again

```text
11010100

↓

11010011

AND

11010000
```

Another **1 disappears**.

Every iteration removes **exactly one set bit**.

If there are **5 ones**, the loop runs **5 times**.

Time Complexity:

```text
O(number of set bits)
```

Very fast.

